Since it looks like you are using the DND tool, my favorite way to do this is to turn the row wrapper (.row-fluid) into a flex layout, and use order on the columns (.span6). Assuming you aren't going to rearrange anything, you can just write a bit of css for this particular page, using the specific .row-number-## class to target only the row you want to change. So -
```@media (max-width: 767px) {
.row-number-12 &gt; .row-fluid {
  display: flex; /* Allows you to rearrange things*/
  flex-flow: wrap; /* Lets child elements wrap */
}
.row-number-12 &gt; .row-fluid &gt; .dnd-column:first-of-type {
    order: 2; /* Move the text, which is in the first column, below the second column */
}
}```
